# PENDING.md - Durable Commitment Tracking

This is an optional workspace file for tracking durable, user-visible commitments that must survive session resets, compaction, and multi-day execution boundaries.

Use this pattern for:
- Follow-up tasks that need to run across multiple days
- Long-running batch jobs that are interrupted by rate limits or timeouts
- Deadlines or check-ins that need to be monitored automatically
- Explicit agreements between operator and agent that should outlive individual sessions

## Example Entries

### API Batch Job - Customer Data Export
- Committed: 2026-04-17
- Deadline: 2026-04-22
- Description: Export 1000 records via rate-limited CRM API (100 requests/hour limit)
- Status: In Progress (800/1000 complete)
- Notes: Cron job resumes exports at 02:00 UTC daily
- Last updated: 2026-04-20

### Monthly Security Audit Follow-Up
- Committed: 2026-04-01
- Deadline: 2026-04-30
- Description: Review security audit logs and generate compliance report
- Status: Not Started
- Notes: Will be triggered by cron on 2026-04-25
- Last updated: 2026-04-01

### Unhandled Support Ticket Follow-Up
- Committed: 2026-04-21
- Deadline: 2026-04-22
- Description: Follow up on ticket #1234 where the user reported a sync failure
- Status: Pending
- Notes: Will check for user updates every 4 hours via heartbeat
- Last updated: 2026-04-21

## Recommended Fields (Optional, No Strict Schema)
- **Task description**: Clear, human-readable summary of the commitment
- **Committed date**: When the commitment was agreed to
- **Deadline**: When the task should be completed by (if applicable)
- **Status**: In Progress / Not Started / Pending / Completed / Blocked
- **Notes**: Any relevant context, scheduling info, or progress updates
- **Last updated**: When this entry was last modified

## Integration with HEARTBEAT.md
You can add a check to your heartbeat configuration to automatically monitor pending commitments:
```yaml
tasks:
  - name: pending-commitment-check
    interval: 30m
    prompt: |
      Read PENDING.md if it exists in the workspace.
      Check all active items for:
      1. Overdue deadlines
      2. Missed checkpoints or status updates
      3. Blocked tasks that need operator attention
      
      If there are actionable items, report them to the user clearly.
      If nothing needs attention, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.
```

## When to Use vs Other Mechanisms
| Mechanism | Use Case |
|-----------|----------|
| **PENDING.md** | Durable, user-visible commitments that need to survive session changes |
| **Background Tasks** | Short-to-medium running execution units that can run in the background |
| **Cron Jobs** | Scheduled, repeating tasks that run at fixed times |
| **Standing Orders** | Persistent authorization for the agent to perform certain actions automatically |
| **HEARTBEAT.md** | Periodic checks and routine maintenance tasks |